  <body>
    <sec id="s1">
      <title>Introduction</title>
      <p>Caffeine (1,3,7-trimethylxanthine) is a stimulant of the central nervous system.</p>
      <p>This review examines the evidence for both beneficial and adverse effects of caffeine consumption.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="s2">
      <title>Methods</title>
      <sec id="s2a">
        <title>Search Strategy</title>
        <p>We searched MEDLINE, Embase, and the Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec id="s2b">
        <title>Selection Criteria</title>
        <p>We included randomized controlled trials and observational studies examining caffeine effects.</p>
      </sec>
    </sec>
    <sec id="s3">
      <title>Results</title>
      <p>We identified 47 studies meeting inclusion criteria.</p>
      <table-wrap id="tbl1">
        <label>Table 1</label>
        <caption>
          <title>Characteristics of Included Studies</title>
          <p>Summary of study design and population characteristics.</p>
        </caption>
        <table>
          <thead>
